##People depressed to the extreme, just want to cry as a life diary of a Wuhan citizen

WECHAT signal NAIPEZLN

Function Introduction, translation and dissemination of ideas, culture, art trends

Foreword

In 2003's SARS, I was studying in Wuhan, everyday two points a line simple life, although also look at the news report, but at that time the network is not developed, the information quantity is very few, Wuhan also infects the human is very few, therefore really does not have any feeling.
The pneumonia epidemic of 2020 broke out in Wuhan -- Foshan, a city of more than 10 million people, where I have lived for nearly 20 years.
Wuhan closed city, the city vehicle ban, soaring prices, medical supplies shortage, the hospital full of patients, a bed difficult to find, medical staff all kinds of despair, Wuhan city government agencies all kinds of inaction. True and false information comes pouring in every day, suffocating people.
From the initial shock, panic, worry and despair to the present calm, every morning and evening to brush the phone, look at all kinds of true or false information, the rest of the time is to play with the children for a while, do housework, then work for a while, as a civilian, can only strictly implement the government's requirements, closed at home, do not give the government trouble, but in fact every day is very suffering, breaking his fingers every day is closed days.
To This Day, my sister in Guangzhou told me that I could write something to record my true feelings these days. I guess so. Although my family and I have been very fortunate so far not to have any medical problems, none of us have been able to stay out of it, which is probably one of the most profound experiences of my life and should be documented.

Wuhan diary

By Yang Dian

The image on the right is "A real-time map of new pneumonia. "
(as of 14:09 a.m. on February 5,2020)

1
Months
18
Shit

I'll never forget this day.

This Day our company held a two-day Group annual meeting. Since New Year's Day, I have been working overtime, did not take a day off, is in order to prepare the group annual meeting needs all kinds of data. The annual meeting means that the end of the phase of work, can finally rest, this is how happy things Ah. But toward the end of the morning meeting, a vice president of the group, after reporting on his work, suddenly spoke to everyone about the "unidentified pneumonia" incident in Wuhan. He told everyone that this "unidentified pneumonia" was by no means the case officially reported, the actual situation is much more serious, we should attach great importance to do a good job of protection, paper can not cover fire. I was stunned and asked a colleague sitting next to me whose husband is from the provincial center for Disease Control and Prevention. She nodded silently and whispered to me that her husband had been quarantined at the Golden Pool Hospital for work, and that one of her colleagues had been infected with the virus, which is highly contagious but can not be disclosed. After listening to her words, I was shocked, completely a sense of being deceived! That's because there have been rumors since late December that an unidentified virus similar to SASR has emerged in Hankou. At that time we are still very serious, the home has prepared some masks, go out to take public transportation I will give the child to wear a mask. But it wasn't until early January that the authorities began to release reports that differed widely from what was reported on the grapevine, and punished those who "spread rumors. ". With all the big events going on at the end of the year, we were completely relaxed. Now I heard that I was a blow, immediately sent Wechat to her husband, let him not to go to the hospital (her husband because of work reasons often go to the hospital) . When I got home in the evening, I told my husband what I had learned. He didn't think much of it. He said, don't be nervous, it's not that scary.

“

January 19th

We're still in the middle of a meeting. To think or feel wrong, I quickly ordered on-line to buy 5 bags of surgical masks, express delivery will soon be directly to the meeting place. Coming home early in the evening, I happened to meet my parents who had to take the bus home every day. I quickly gave them some masks and said something about "pneumonia unknown" . They had to wear masks when they took the bus. My husband came home soon and told me that something was wrong. Today, he saw a lot of medical staff in full armor and chemical-resistant clothes. Again, I emphasized what I knew, and he was a little skeptical, saying that the government couldn't hide something like this, or something big would happen.

”

1
Months
20
Shit

Back to the office, one into the office to see colleagues gathered to say this "pneumonia" thing, the same day Wuhan notification increased a number of cases, and the wording has changed. I told them what I knew and told them to go down to the nearest pharmacy immediately to buy face masks, Oseltamivir, lotus seeds and other supplies. A few colleagues in the office went doubtfully, and soon came up with a large bag of things, saying that the drugstore had a lot of things. I don't know what to say. People still don't realize it. By midday, however, information was beginning to pour in. After lunch, office colleagues felt less mask to buy, said to buy some more, but soon came back, said the drugstore no mask, even no drugs, and regret not to buy more in the morning. The situation became so serious that we immediately cancelled the planned evening departmental dinner. In the evening, I told my husband about the arrangements for the Spring Festival. A month ago, we had booked a train ticket back and forth to my husband's hometown. I said this is a serious situation, you'd better talk to your family, see if they mind, if you go back to the infected virus that is more embarrassing. My husband was very angry, said there is no, we are not sick, and even if sick, which parents have abandoned their children? My Speechless (TV series) 

“

21 January

On our last day at work, many of our out-of-town colleagues had already gone home on leave early. By this time there had been a lot of information about pneumonia, new cases began to proliferate, especially on the evening of 20, academician Zhong Nanshan confirmed for the first time that the virus will be "human to human" information. The situation became not optimistic, I thought about it, or directly contacted my husband's sister, said the current epidemic in Wuhan, the risk of taking public transport, but also let them discuss, carefully consider whether we can accept to go back? Afternoon back home, the husband Livid Face Sitting on the SOFA, see me to say, his family according to my instructions spirit call him, told us not to go back. Although I understand his heart to go home for the new year, but also angry, one can not be too selfish, go back to take the train risk, also with a 9-year-old child, but also go home to the family risk is great. I give him reason, but he does not listen, always feel this is I do not want to go back to his home to find an excuse for the new year, so we had a quarrel, break up!

”

1
Months
22
Shit

The atmosphere at home is not good, my husband can not accept the temporary change of plans not to go home for the New Year, according to the plan we are the afternoon of the train, until nearly noon, he saw me no change, reluctantly returned the ticket.

“

January 23rd

Early in the morning by the online news of the closure of Wuhan to the shock. My husband and I looked at each other and realized that the situation might be worse than we thought. I'm glad I let my parents live in my house two days ago. It's always good to be a family. After a quick wash, she and her husband put on a mask and ran to the supermarket nearest to their home (as they were going home for the New Year, they didn't have a lot of supplies) . When they entered the supermarket, they were frightened by the crowd in the vegetable area. There were too many people, moreover, there was nothing on the shelves. A worker had just brought a box of vegetables from the reservoir area. Before they reached the shelves, they had already been robbed by the crowd. Long lines snaked and twisted, each pushing a large trailer, line up full of stuff, weigh it, haggle over prices. What do we do? The panic surrounding the siege has spread, and everything has to be taken. My husband and I discussed, I pushed the trailer to the end of the line, he was responsible for grabbing food. What a time it is, watching all the armed men, the anxiety in their eyes and the fear they can't hide, my heart is bleeding. After nearly two hours of struggle, the trailer was loaded with Shanghai Greens, carrots, cucumbers and peppers, bags of flour and frozen chicken, and we returned home sweaty. I went home to wash my face and change my clothes, so that I could count the stuff in the fridge, and it would last for a week. You know what? It's GonNa be better. We all do.

In the afternoon, I had a good sleep, got up and went out to wear a mask, found that I had bought 5 bags of masks before only two bags left? I was shocked, now the mask is a seriously scarce supplies, AH, this is my foresight to buy a life-saving thing AH, in panic, my husband came in the door, looked at me and immediately said to me, he took two packs of masks to the doctor of the Provincial People's Hospital and took them. He saw the message from the doctor about the shortage of materials and asked for help. So he took the two packs and sent them over on his own initiative. He also said that the doctor was going to cry after he got them. What can I say? Doctors need masks more than we do, and they're on the front lines, but we don't have enough masks!

On the first day of the siege, we lived in fear.

”

The timeline was curated by an online friend

1
Months
24
Shit

Ōmisoka. Everyone was in a bad mood except the children, who were happily watching TV. The messages sent from various wechat groups, especially the videos of hospitals in Wuhan running low on supplies and full of patients, are depressing. The fear that you or your family will become one of them, that if your elderly parents get infected, they will be separated from you. And as our company belongs to the medical industry, has set up a special epidemic materials coordination team in the first time, responsible for helping the major hospitals to snap up, distribution of materials. But look at the information in the group is really not optimistic, the major subsidiary warehouse of the related material inventory has been completely emptied, and the imported materials simply can not come in because the city closed, because I sent a car to pick up the goods should also be various formalities to go through and various cards...

But we still have to eat new year's meals, and life goes on. In the evening I did not see the Spring Festival gala, always feel those happy scenes have nothing to do with us, sad, heartache! I don't want to talk to my husband, who's there now and then, cursing the Wuhan government.

“

25 January

For days, the weather in Wuhan was as brutal as the epidemic, rainy, cold and damp.

New Year's Day, a group of colleagues in the Department said, 2-year-old child fever, do not know how to do? She was advised not to take the child to hospital, the risk is high, and there is no doctor to see. She worried that the child has contracted the virus, said in despair has written a will, intends to take the child to the hospital... ... We have no choice but to pray for her child well. Fortunately, she found a community clinic, to the child injection, the child also reduced fever, false alarm.

Wuhan has issued a traffic ban, meaning all motor vehicles will be banned from the roads. It doesn't really mean anything to those of us who aren't sick. But for the sick, the message said that each community had been assigned a taxi, sending out the license plate number and the driver's contact information. But how is it possible to see a neighborhood this big, with at least tens of thousands of people, in one taxi? It's completely idiotic!

These days the amount of information is very large, on the Internet, television is all Wuhan city government officials all kinds of embarrassing performance, see people speechless, people ashamed and angry. I'm not a native of Wuhan, but I've been in Wuhan for almost 20 years, and I've made the city my home, and Wuhan has grown rapidly over the years, changing the way it used to be, especially with the Military World Games in October, the whole city has changed a lot, the overall quality of the residents has also improved a lot compared to the past, from the bottom of my heart I love this city, hope it is better! But look at the performance of these government officials at the press conference, one figure is not clear, one fat, irresponsible nonsense said that five million people left Wuhan, causing the whole people to curse, it is absolutely heart-wrenching! And look at the government in the face of this epidemic, it is completely headless, chaotic, one measure at a time, one order at a time, not to mention those functional departments, even we ordinary people have been rounded up at a loss!

”

1
Months
26
Shit

There is a group of colleagues out on leave in advance of the New Year sent a message asking how to return to Wuhan? Says he's been discriminated against and he just wants to go home. Think about the Internet is full of scold Wuhan People's Posts and countless unknown and in the city a few days before the Han people left the wandering, the blame, the heart is very hard! We are also just ordinary people. We don't eat game, we don't do anything harmful to nature, and we are also victims. But now, because of the inaction of the Wuhan Municipal Government, we have become the people despised by the whole nation, and we have become the source of this disaster, bring disaster to the people of the whole country and even the whole world! Shame, grievance, worry, fear, all kinds of feelings indescribable!

“

27 January

On the 5th day of the siege of Wuhan, the weather was still cold and overcast. In the evening, a message was sent out from the community group. The self-organized residents of Wuhan who are isolated at home will start singing the national anthem and "my Motherland" at 8 PM TO CHEER FOR WUHAN! I pulled myself together and looked out the window at the brightly lit building of Zhongnan Hospital and the "I love Hubei, Wuhan, go for it" playing on the neon sign outside the Hanxiu theater? At 8:00, as expected, the deafening sound of singing outside the window, rough, weak, immature, one after another, think of just seen in the group of a hospital doctor with a phone shouting video, my tears. What could possibly have caused this? I was so depressed, I just wanted to cry..

”

The cartoon was written by "Chen Xiaotao Momo" (Weibo ID) 

1
Months
30
Shit

An employee in the company group sent out a distress message saying that he had been diagnosed with coronavirus, but there had been no beds for him to enter the hospital. He had passed out several times at home and could not do so even after calling 120.120 said that he could not come until he was admitted to a certain hospital, i had no choice but to call the company for help, to see who can find a bed. Leaders with the resources began to think positively, but the feedback was not good. According to the current admissions process in Wuhan, families can only be admitted to a designated hospital in a designated area and must be reported through the community, but the hospital is full, there are no beds, and even if some new hospitals are added, they are either not ready to accept it or soon will be full. A leader in the group said that now a large third-class hospital doctors family members are seriously ill can not be admitted to their own hospital, not to mention the power of ordinary people? One bed is hard to find, and I can feel a deep sense of despair through the screen of my mobile phone. I prayed for my health and that of my family, and finally realized that the number of people infected in Wuhan far exceeded the public figures. In the evening, there was information that a neighbor had been unable to enter the hospital because of a fever. Now the elderly father has passed away, and the family members have developed symptoms and are quarantined at home by themselves, so everyone must be careful and take precautions. I was in tears at the news, Zombie, and seemed to be glad for those who had fled Wuhan before the siege, at least if they were really sick, there would be a hospital to go to, and a doctor to help you, so what if they are discriminated against? It's better than staying at home in Wuhan and waiting to die?

I'll never forget this day.

This Day our company held a two-day Group annual meeting. Since New Year's Day, I have been working overtime, did not take a day off, is in order to prepare the group annual meeting needs all kinds of data. The annual meeting means that the end of the phase of work, can finally rest, this is how happy things Ah. But toward the end of the morning meeting, a vice president of the group, after reporting on his work, suddenly spoke to everyone about the "unidentified pneumonia" incident in Wuhan. He told everyone that this "unidentified pneumonia" was by no means the case officially reported, the actual situation is much more serious, we should attach great importance to do a good job of protection, paper can not cover fire. I was stunned and asked a colleague sitting next to me whose husband is from the provincial center for Disease Control and Prevention. She nodded silently and whispered to me that her husband had been quarantined at the Golden Pool Hospital for work, and that one of her colleagues had been infected with the virus, which is highly contagious but can not be disclosed. After listening to her words, I was shocked, completely a sense of being deceived! That's because there have been rumors since late December that an unidentified virus similar to SASR has emerged in Hankou. At that time we are still very serious, the home has prepared some masks, go out to take public transportation I will give the child to wear a mask. But it wasn't until early January that the authorities began to release reports that differed widely from what was reported on the grapevine, and punished those who "spread rumors. ". With all the big events going on at the end of the year, we were completely relaxed. Now I heard that I was a blow, immediately sent Wechat to her husband, let him not to go to the hospital (her husband because of work reasons often go to the hospital) . When I got home in the evening, I told my husband what I had learned. He didn't think much of it. He said, don't be nervous, it's not that scary.

The situation became not optimistic, I thought about it, or directly contacted my husband's sister, said the current epidemic in Wuhan, the risk of taking public transport, but also let them discuss, carefully consider whether we can accept to go back? Afternoon back home, the husband Livid Face Sitting on the SOFA, see me to say, his family according to my instructions spirit call him, told us not to go back. Although I understand his heart to go home for the new year, but also angry, one can not be too selfish, go back to take the train risk, also with a 9-year-old child, but also go home to the family risk is great. I give him reason, but he does not listen, always feel this is I do not want to go back to his home to find an excuse for the new year, so we had a quarrel, break up!

“

January 23rd

Early in the morning by the online news of the closure of Wuhan to the shock. My husband and I looked at each other and realized that the situation might be worse than we thought. I'm glad I let my parents live in my house two days ago. It's always good to be a family. After a quick wash, she and her husband put on a mask and ran to the supermarket nearest to their home (as they were going home for the New Year, they didn't have a lot of supplies) . When they entered the supermarket, they were frightened by the crowd in the vegetable area. There were too many people, moreover, there was nothing on the shelves. A worker had just brought a box of vegetables from the reservoir area. Before they reached the shelves, they had already been robbed by the crowd. Long lines snaked and twisted, each pushing a large trailer, line up full of stuff, weigh it, haggle over prices. What do we do? The panic surrounding the siege has spread, and everything has to be taken. My husband and I discussed, I pushed the trailer to the end of the line, he was responsible for grabbing food. What a time it is, watching all the armed men, the anxiety in their eyes and the fear they can't hide, my heart is bleeding. After nearly two hours of struggle, the trailer was loaded with Shanghai Greens, carrots, cucumbers and peppers, bags of flour and frozen chicken, and we returned home sweaty. I went home to wash my face and change my clothes, so that I could count the stuff in the fridge, and it would last for a week. You know what? It's GonNa be better. We all do.

In the afternoon, I had a good sleep, got up and went out to wear a mask, found that I had bought 5 bags of masks before only two bags left? I was shocked, now the mask is a seriously scarce supplies, AH, this is my foresight to buy a life-saving thing AH, in panic, my husband came in the door, looked at me and immediately said to me, he took two packs of masks to the doctor of the Provincial People's Hospital and took them. He saw the message from the doctor about the shortage of materials and asked for help. So he took the two packs and sent them over on his own initiative. He also said that the doctor was going to cry after he got them. What can I say? Doctors need masks more than we do, and they're on the front lines, but we don't have enough masks!

On the first day of the siege, we lived in fear.

25 January

For days, the weather in Wuhan was as brutal as the epidemic, rainy, cold and damp.

New Year's Day, a group of colleagues in the Department said, 2-year-old child fever, do not know how to do? She was advised not to take the child to hospital, the risk is high, and there is no doctor to see. She worried that the child has contracted the virus, said in despair has written a will, intends to take the child to the hospital... ... We have no choice but to pray for her child well. Fortunately, she found a community clinic, to the child injection, the child also reduced fever, false alarm.

Wuhan has issued a traffic ban, meaning all motor vehicles will be banned from the roads. It doesn't really mean anything to those of us who aren't sick. But for the sick, the message said that each community had been assigned a taxi, sending out the license plate number and the driver's contact information. But how is it possible to see a neighborhood this big, with at least tens of thousands of people, in one taxi? It's completely idiotic!

These days the amount of information is very large, on the Internet, television is all Wuhan city government officials all kinds of embarrassing performance, see people speechless, people ashamed and angry. I'm not a native of Wuhan, but I've been in Wuhan for almost 20 years, and I've made the city my home, and Wuhan has grown rapidly over the years, changing the way it used to be, especially with the Military World Games in October, the whole city has changed a lot, the overall quality of the residents has also improved a lot compared to the past, from the bottom of my heart I love this city, hope it is better! But look at the performance of these government officials at the press conference, one figure is not clear, one fat, irresponsible nonsense said that five million people left Wuhan, causing the whole people to curse, it is absolutely heart-wrenching! And look at the government in the face of this epidemic, it is completely headless, chaotic, one measure at a time, one order at a time, not to mention those functional departments, even we ordinary people have been rounded up at a loss!

27 January

On the 5th day of the siege of Wuhan, the weather was still cold and overcast. In the evening, a message was sent out from the community group. The self-organized residents of Wuhan who are isolated at home will start singing the national anthem and "my Motherland" at 8 PM TO CHEER FOR WUHAN! I pulled myself together and looked out the window at the brightly lit building of Zhongnan Hospital and the "I love Hubei, Wuhan, go for it" playing on the neon sign outside the Hanxiu theater? At 8:00, as expected, the deafening sound of singing outside the window, rough, weak, immature, one after another, think of just seen in the group of a hospital doctor with a phone shouting video, my tears. What could possibly have caused this? I was so depressed, I just wanted to cry..

Months
30
Shit

An employee in the company group sent out a distress message saying that he had been diagnosed with coronavirus, but there had been no beds for him to enter the hospital. He had passed out several times at home and could not do so even after calling 120.120 said that he could not come until he was admitted to a certain hospital, i had no choice but to call the company for help, to see who can find a bed. Leaders with the resources began to think positively, but the feedback was not good. According to the current admissions process in Wuhan, families can only be admitted to a designated hospital in a designated area and must be reported through the community, but the hospital is full, there are no beds, and even if some new hospitals are added, they are either not ready to accept it or soon will be full. A leader in the group said that now a large third-class hospital doctors family members are seriously ill can not be admitted to their own hospital, not to mention the power of ordinary people? One bed is hard to find, and I can feel a deep sense of despair through the screen of my mobile phone. I prayed for my health and that of my family, and finally realized that the number of people infected in Wuhan far exceeded the public figures. In the evening, there was information that a neighbor had been unable to enter the hospital because of a fever. Now the elderly father has passed away, and the family members have developed symptoms and are quarantined at home by themselves, so everyone must be careful and take precautions. I was in tears at the news, Zombie, and seemed to be glad for those who had fled Wuhan before the siege, at least if they were really sick, there would be a hospital to go to, and a doctor to help you, so what if they are discriminated against? It's better than staying at home in Wuhan and waiting to die?
